sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant T as Telegram API
    participant n8n
    participant FS as File System

    %% Workflow 5 - Scan start

    U->>T: send /start (or manual start in n8n)

    Note over n8n: Workflow 5 - Manual Trigger
    n8n->>FS: Execute Command: nohup process.py (in background)
    n8n->>T: Telegram: "scan started" (fixed Chat ID)
    T-->>U: start confirmation

    Note over FS: process.py in background
    FS->>FS: scan files in WORKSPACE_PATH (recursive)
    FS->>FS: write pid.txt + processed.csv in /tmp/workflow5/
    FS->>FS: at the end call monitor.py --format md
    FS->>T: process.py: send final summary (urllib, fixed Chat ID)
    T-->>U: scan completed summary

    %% Workflow 6 - Ongoing monitoring

    U->>T: send /status (or other)

    Note over n8n: Workflow 6 - Schedule Trigger (every minute)
    n8n->>T: getUpdates (Node 2 - HTTP Request)
    T-->>n8n: list of recent messages

    n8n->>n8n: Node 3 - Code: filter recent messages

    alt /status
        n8n->>n8n: Node 4 - Switch → /status branch
        n8n->>FS: Execute Command: monitor.py --format md --data /tmp/workflow5
        FS-->>n8n: formatted Markdown message
        n8n->>T: Node D - Telegram: send status (fixed Chat ID)
        T-->>U: ongoing scan status
    else fallback
        n8n->>n8n: Node 4 - Switch → Fallback Output
        n8n->>n8n: Node 5 - IF: text matches regex
        n8n->>T: Node 6 - Telegram: send reply (fixed Chat ID)
        T-->>U: automatic reply
    end
